body:
Modern [b]Tribal Illustration[/b] has its roots in tattoo and tiki-bar culture, which was inspired, in turn, by Polynesian designs of ancient origins.

title: ueki-chan
body:
[b]Ueki-chan[/b] (from 植木 or うえき, meaning plant) is a Room Item designed by [[Miyamoto Frederica]]'s voice actor, Takano Asami, for [i][[idolmaster cinderella girls starlight stage|THE IDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls: Starlight Stage]][/i].

As part of a promotional web talk show, the voice actresses of the series participate in a Room Item Design Competition, where each of the hosts design and draw their own Room Item. The drawing voted highest by viewers gets implemented into [i]Starlight Stage[/i]. On May 18th, 2016, on the broadcast promoting [[tulip_(idolmaster)|Tulip]]'s CD release, Takano Asami submitted her drawing of what she called Ueki-chan, a large potted [[tulip]] costume that idols could wear, with her character, Miyamoto Frederica, wearing it as an example. The peculiar design, incorporating what looked like a tree trunk into what was supposed to be a tulip, as well as the particular way Frederica's face was drawn, drew an immediate reaction from both viewers and the other co-hosts that was compounded even more when the design won. The victory seemed to surprise even Asami, who issued an apology herself when the hosts returned after the following segment. Ueki-chan was nevertheless implemented, though the game version does not incorporate the costume aspect of the item, and instead bears Asami's rendition of Frederica's face by default.

The item has since become infamous, appearing not only in fan art, but also as a doodle on the log-in screen for [i]Starlight Stage[/i], and even receiving its own merchandise.

h4. External Links

title: yorita_yoshino
body:
An [i][[iDOLMASTER Cinderella Girls|iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls]][/i] character in the Passion (Yellow Sun) category. She is a mysterious girl who goes out of her way to help strangers, speaking and acting as if she's more than just an ordinary person. Her manner of speech, in addition to being very slow and soft, is highly elaborate and old-fashioned, making her sound more like a historical priestess than a modern-day girl: in particular she is known for ending her sentences with でして (deshite), which is regarded as a formal or old-fashioned form of です (desu).

Yoshino has an interest in shrines and temples, which suggests that before becoming an idol she was a miko - however it is heavily implied (due to her ability to resolve people's wishes and find lost items) that she is some form of supernatural entity, possibly the goddess Benzaiten (one of the Seven Lucky Gods or shichifukuji), as several of Yoshino's illustrations show her having a connection to water; in addition to fortune, music and words, Benzaiten is the goddess of water. If that is the case, then the Producer successfully talked a goddess into becoming an idol - although it's possible that she does it just because she enjoys being worshipped.

She is voiced by [[Takada Yuuki]].

title: pikario_(precure)
body:
[[Kirakira Precure a la Mode]] character. A fairy who is the twin brother of [[kirarin (precure)|Kirarin]]. He was initially corrupted into the sinister villain [[julio (precure)|Julio]] through influence from Noir, but he was later purified by the Cures and helps [[Kirahoshi Ciel]] create her Animal Sweet before fading away. He spends the rest of his time resting in Ichigo Mountain.

Pikario later makes a reappearance starting from episode 39, where his time in Ichigo Mountain has restored his strength and grants him a [[magical boy]]-like form to help aid the Cures. He now spends his time in human form getting reacquainted with Ciel.

Like Julio, Pikario has [[long hair|long]] [[blue hair]] and [[green eyes]] in human form. He keeps it in a [[low ponytail]] unlike his evil counterpart, and ties his hair with a similar garnish ornament to  Ciel. In fairy form, he looks identical to Kirarin save for his hair going the opposite direction.

h4. See also
* [[Cure Waffle]]

title: houchou_toushirou
body:
A [i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i] character. One of the Awataguchi school swords and thus is one of the many "Toushirou" brothers. 

Has a thing for sweets and married women. Having been owned by Tokugawa Ieyasu, his liking for married women is a reference to Ieyasu's reputation as a womanizer. In fandom, this very quickly snowballed into Houchou either being the only skirt chaser of the citadel, openly lusting after particularly effeminate-looking or wife-like swords (such as [[Horikawa Kunihiro]]) if there is an absence of a [[female saniwa (touken ranbu)|female saniwa]] or women in general, or indulging in [[netorare]]. After a while a lot of fanworks just portrayed him as a needy kid, with the implication that he goes after married women then being due to the fact that they're more likely to give him candy.

He has [[brown hair]] and [[brown eyes]]. He wears a [[military uniform]] with [[shorts]] like his brothers, though with a yellow [[necktie]] instead of a black one. He wears colorful [[japanese_armor|Japanese armor]] consisting of [[sode]] and [[kote]] on his right side. He wears a pink [[hairclip]] in his hair and carries a [[messenger bag]], which his damaged portrait reveals is full of [[candy]].

Voiced by [[Miyata Kouki]]. Artist is [[kumita (sumica)]].

title: atlantic_mackerel
body:
A species of mackerel. Sold in Japan as [i]Taiseiyou saba[/i] (literal translation from English), Norwegian mackerel ([i]Norway saba[/i]),  or simply mackerel ([i]saba[/i], a general term for [i]Scomber[/i], [i]Rastrelliger[/i] and [i]Grammatorcynus[/i]). Also known as Boston mackerel or Scottish mackerel.

"The Atlantic mackerel's body is elongate, steel-blue marked with wavy black lines dorsally and silvery-white ventrally, its snout long and pointed. It possesses two spiny dorsal fins, which are spaced far apart, two pectoral fins, and small caudal and anal fins, also spaced far apart." [1]

h4. See also

* [[Fish]]
* Not to be confused with the [[okhotsk atka mackerel]].

title: maou_(maoyuu)
body:
"Demon Queen"

The female lead protagonist. The 43rd ruler of the Demon World and the youngest to rule by demon standards, she is a powerful sorceress but has no experience in battle. Wise and smart, her vast knowledge comes from the "Exterior Library", a hidden dimension where knowledge of the past and future is kept and where her clan lived. Despite her knowledge, she is considered incompetent by the warmongering demon clans. Seeing what would happen to the war if it didn't end without the problems that it cause fixed, she awaited the arrival of the [[yuusha_(maoyuu)|Hero]] so she could ask for his help to end war the right way. After finally getting him as her ally, she and the Hero travel to the Human world where she takes the identity of the "Crimson Scholar", a human noble who has come to help the lower classes.

See also:

* [[Maoyuu Maou Yuusha]]
* [[maid-chou_(maoyuu)|Maid-Chou]]

title: yuusha_(maoyuu)
body:
"Hero"

The male lead protagonist. A young and powerful human warrior, he came to the Demon World to end the evil of the demons by killing their leader, the [[maou_(maoyuu)|Demon Queen]]. Instead, he learns the harsh reality the Human/Demon war was never a battle between Good and Evil but a period of turmoil where both weak, innocent humans and demons are oppressed and taken advantage by the corrupt and powerful from both sides. Wishing to end the war the right way with the least repercussions, he agrees to become the Demon Queen's ally in her plans to stop the war.

title: lancia_delta_s4
body:
Lancia's Delta S4 was a rally car developed for the WRC's short-lived Group B category, where the cars had a massive power output compared to their Group A counterparts. Like all Group B rally cara it had a civilian version called the Delta S4 Stradale.

It had an Abarth tuned 1,759 cc inline-4 engine, which produced 550 horsepower; made possible by the use of a turbocharger and supercharger; a system called twin-charging.

The S4 made it's debut at the 1985 event of the RAC Rally (now called the Wales Rally GB) and won that event; at the hands of up-and-coming Finnish rally driver Henri Toivonen; who also won the Monte Carlo Rally of 1986.

Sadly however, with so much unfulfilled potential left, Toivonen and his co-driver Sergio Cresto; both died in the 1986 Tour de Corse, when their S4 Delta missed a tight left-hand hairpin and plunged off into a wooded ravine and exploded in flames; leaving only the badly burnt spaceframe and chassis. The crash was nearly a year after Lancia's Attilio Bettega died after crashing his Lancia 037 (the car that was replaced by the S4.)

A comment made by Cesare Fiorio, then team boss of the Lancia rally team, just told of how much unfulfilled potential Henri Toivonen still had to show; as he was the only driver on the team who could control Lancia's S4 Delta but Toivonen himself said that the car had a mind of it's own and that he himself didn't know how to drive it.

title: saigusa_haruka
body:
A Character from [[little_busters!|Little Busters!]]. Haruka is a schoolmate of Riki's from a different class, but despite this, always seems to find time to hang around in Riki's classroom. She is a problem child and will start an uproar for her own personal enjoyment, which causes her twin sister, the public morals chairman Kanata Futaki, to often chase after her. She use marbles as a weapon to distract the public morals committee from chasing her, and when Riki is with her, she will drag Riki away, explaining that being captured by the public morals committee means big trouble for her. [spoiler]The truth is, she was abused by her family (not her parents, who were kept away from her and Kanata), while Kanata was seemingly treated very well, though truthfully she was not. She thus starts trouble to bother her sister and shame her family name.[/spoiler] She works part-time in the school's cafeteria to get permission to use the oven to bake muffins and cakes.

title: sonderkommando_elbe
body:
Named "Special Command Elbe" after the river where it's headquarters was near to; this special unit of the Luftwaffe employed the exact opposite of the earlier Sturmböcke units; by using stripped down Messerschmitt Bf-109G fighters (excess armor and armament except a single MG131) for use as ramming USAAF heavy bombers.

The unit only saw one combat mission on 7th of April, 1945 with a sortie by 180 pilots, but recorded only 15 US bombers destroyed and 8 of their own planes lost. 

Unlike the kamikaze units of the Japanese; Elbe pilots only had a lightly armored Bf-109G plus a 13mm machine gun with only 60 bullets (only a few Elbe pilots used this to successfully down US bombers) , but used the propeller of their aircraft to physically damage US bombers.

title: sturmbock_(unit)
body:
When USAAF heavy bombers started appearing they caused problems for the Luftwaffe's fighter force, whose armaments at the time could not adequately destroy B-17s and B-24s deployed in the combat box formation. And fighter escort usage meant the earlier solution using Bf110 bomber destroyers was no longer viable.

So the decision was made to modify the rugged Focke Wulf 190 into a bomber interceptor, modifying it with heavier armaments including 30mm cannons and unguided rockets plus heavy armor; but these rendered the planes cumbersome and useless without fighter escort.

title: sentinel_(x-men)
body:
An [[X-Men]] type of villain that is well known for its appearance in the [[Marvel vs. Capcom]] series.

In the [[Marvel]] universe the [b]Sentinel[/b] is a type of [[giant]] humanoid sentient [[robot]] or [[mecha]] designed for hunting down super-powered mutants.

They are very powerful and have energy weapons built on their hands as well as telescopic robotic tentacles designed to capture their prey. The Sentinels are usually deployed in vast numbers.

There is a [[meme]] involving Sentinel's orange and blue palette in [[Marvel vs. Capcom 3]] called "Mango Sentinel", due to how its armor resembles the color of [[mango]] flesh.
